body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

Consider the following code:
``` verilog
module test (in, out); 
  input [3:0] in;  
  output [3:0] out; 
  integer i; 
  always @(*) begin
    for (i = 0; i < 4; i = i + 1) begin
      out[i] = in[i];
      i = i + 1;
      out[i] = ~in[i];
    end
  end
endmodule
```
And process it with:
``` shell
read test.v
hierarchy -top test
proc; opt; techmap; opt;
show
```
## Expected behavior
I'd expect the behavior of verilog after simplification to look something like:
``` verilog
module test (in, out); 
  input [3:0] in;  
  output [3:0] out; 
  always @(*) begin
    out[0] = in[0];
    out[1] = ~in[1];
    out[2] = in[2];
    out[3] = ~in[3];
  end
endmodule
```
## Actual behavior
Instead, I get:
``` verilog
module test (in, out); 
  input [3:0] in;  
  output [3:0] out; 
  always @(*) begin
    out[0] = ~in[0];
    out[1] = ~in[1];
    out[2] = ~in[2];
    out[3] = ~in[3];
  end
endmodule
```
